There appears to be a bug in Jasmine v1.1.0, where if a waitsFor block times out, jasmine.WaitsForBlock#execute() calls the following:
this.spec.fail({
  name: 'timeout',
  message: message
});
(See WaitsForBlock.js line 40)
Unfortunately, jasmine.Spec#fail() requires that its argument is a proper error -- specifically, an object with a stack property. (See Spec.js line 124).
This results in the following error if you call a waitsFor that times out: Uncaught TypeError: Cannot read property 'stack' of undefined.

