I discovered the Jasmine Data Provider is not compatible with Jasmine 2.0. I've forked master and am working on this. It would support data driven tests like this:
all("blank values are invalid", [ "", " ", "\t", " \t\n", "\n", null ], function(x) {
    expect(isBlank(x)).toBe(true);
});
You can specify multiple arguments:
all("foo", [ [1,2], [3,4] ], function(x, y) {
    ...
});
And do asynchronous tests:
all("foo", [1, 2, 3], function(x, done) {
    setTimeout(function() {
        ...
        done();
    }, 500);
});
It would get expanded into multliple it's:
foo (Variant #0 <1>)
foo (Variant #1 <2>)
foo (Variant #2 <3>)

And of course you could mark them all pending:
xall("foo", [ ... ], function(x) {
    ...
});
A pull request should be coming up in the next few days.

