Jasmine works this way to allow specs like:
spyOn(anObject, 'aMethod').and.returnValue('aValue');
somethingThatCalls();
anObject.aMethod.and.throwError('Oops');
somethingElseThatCalls();
By replacing the previous spy strategy when you set one, we're able to have the code be consistent across all strategies.
That said, I see the desire for something like this, but I think passing the return values as multiple parameters to and.returnValue would allow it to continue to behave similar to the other strategies. If you want to put together a pull request that does something like that, I'd be happy to review it.

