We're throwing an error in this case under the assumption that you've probably mistakenly called createSpyObj. The line you have
b = jasmine.createSpyObj('b', []);
ends up being exactly equivalent to:
b = {};
because if you don't pass in any method names, no spies are actually created on the object. Given this, this isn't functionality we're likely to change.

If you want to create an empty spy/mock in typescript for testing:
let x: T = <T>{};
