Jasmine spies save all of the arguments for each invokation by default. So, in your example, you should be able to check the same things with:
// args is an array of all the arguments
xxx.yyy.calls.mostRecent().args
or in an expectation:
expect(xxx.yyy).toHaveBeenCalledWith(foo, bar, baz);
Given this, it is unclear to me how your proposed setParams would be different.

Using calls.mostRecent().args or calls.argsFor(2) to get the list of arguments for only a specific call to the fake should be more reliable that you're getting the correct args. Getting myMethod set like this as in your earlier example would look something like:
var myMethod = xxx.yyy.calls.mostRecent().args[0];
It seems like this should solve the same problem.

