As describe here, this behavior appear when some of the spec are loaded before the browser raises the window load event.
The subsequent window.onload cause the spec to be executed multiple times.
The solution suggested in the stackoverflow question above (remove .then(window.onload)), doesn't work for the spec that doesn't get to be loaded before the browser raises the window load event.
One (ugly) workaround that I find is to retard the execution of the spec like this:
setTimeout(function(){ 
    Promise.all([
        System.import('app/1st.spec'),
        System.import('app/my-uppercase.pipe.spec')
    ])   
    .then(window.onload)
    .catch(console.error.bind(console));
}, 1000);

