Your problem is that you are calling your function in your test, so it blows up before it has a chance to match. toThrow takes a function and calls it itself.
You can either do:
expect(code.throw_error).toThrow();
or if you need arguments:
expect(function () {
 code.throw_error(1,2,3) 
}).toThrow();

