This is more so related to #1216... but since that was closed I figured I'd add it here:
Looking at the source code for 2.5.2, I see:
function Jasmine(options) {
...
this.reporter = new module.exports.ConsoleReporter();
this.env.addReporter(this.reporter);
...
}
With this change, we are no longer able to use configureDefaultReporter to configure the default ConsoleReporter, since a console reporter (without any configuration) is already added when Jasmine is initiated, which explains the issue in #1216.
Relating to this issue, as noted above by @lonelyelk, this also means that this console reporter will not be replaced by a custom reporter, unless you clear the console reporter by calling jasmine.env.clearReporters() and then adding the desired reporter.

