To get similar functionality, I used a work around that I found on issue #1377 of Jest.
it('to throw error', async () => {
    let errorMessage = 'No error thrown.';
    try {
        await functionToThrowError();
    } catch (error) {
        errorMessage = error.message;
    }
    expect(errorMessage).toBe('An error was thrown.');
});

You can use https://jasmine.github.io/api/3.3/async-matchers.html:
await expectAsync(aPromise).toBeRejected();
