Unfortunately, functions are really hard to do equality comparisons on. For example, this spec fails:
it("can't compare functions", function()  {
  expect(function() {}).toEqual(function() {});
});
Because functions are compared via reference equality
it('does reference equality', function()  {
  var fn = function() {};
  expect(fn).toEqual(fn);
});
Depending on what you're looking to test about the function, you might also look at jasmine.any(Function), which you can also nest inside your jasmine.objectContaining.
Hope this helps. Thanks for using Jasmine!

