expect(() => await promise).toThrowError('demo');

// This won't work either! it doesn't throw, it rejects
expect(async () => await promise).toThrowError('demo');
For some reason I thought there was a way to collapse an awaited promise into a toThrowError matcher, but I think there isn't.

